Parliament, Thursday, 14 March 2019 – The Ad Hoc Committee to identify suitable candidates for the filling of vacancies at the Commission for Gender Equality (CGE) concluded its process of interviewing shortlisted candidates. The committee will meet and deliberate on the candidates and thereafter recommend names to The Presidency. The committee shortlisted 24 candidates to be interviewed for appointment to the Commission for Gender Equality. The committee will recommend names for the filling of eight vacancies. The committee will today (Thursday, 14 March 2019) meet and deliberate on the candidates. Details of the meeting: Committee Room V475, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building, at 12 pm. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE AD HOC COMMITTEE TO IDENTIFY SUITABLE CANDIDATES FOR THE FILLING OF VACANCIES AT THE COMMISSION FOR GENDER EQUALITY, MS NONHLANHLA NCUBE-NDABA.
